OL,3,CMum fears daughter's ME death could
OL,4,C'too easily' happen to someone else
OL,6,FMs Boothby - becoming emotional - went
OL,7,Fon to say that Maeve told her she
OL,8,Fdidn't want to die in hospital.
OL,10,F"She wanted only a loving hug. By then
OL,11,Fit was too late - all touch was
OL,12,Fexcruciatingly painful.
OL,14,FMiss Boothby added: "By this stage
OL,15,FMaeve was starving to death. She knew
OL,16,Fit, I knew it, her father knew it, we
OL,17,Fknew it, the GP knew it.
OL,26,@vD@UOU
