OL,3,CMum fears daughter's ME death could
OL,4,C'too easily' happen to someone else
OL,6,F"How the hospital did not recognise
OL,7,Fthis as the inevitable outcome of
OL,8,Finadequate hydration and nutrition
OL,9,Fmust be for them to answer.
OL,11,F"After Maeve died, GP Dr Lucy Shenton
OL,12,Ftold me she had never seen anyone so
OL,13,Fbadly treated by the NHS."
OL,15,FRhys Hadden, representing the hospital
OL,16,Ftrust, told assistant coroner Deborah
OL,17,FArcher his client did not accept all
OL,18,Fof Miss Boothby's evidence.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUuD@ZO]
