OL,6,FMaeve's father, the Times journalist
OL,7,FSean O'Neill, also gave evidence at
OL,8,Fher inquest today.
OL,10,FHe began reading the statement, but
OL,11,Fbecame too emotional to continue, and
OL,12,Fso it was read out by the coroner.
OL,14,FMr O'Neill said: "I am full of
OL,15,Fmemories of Maeve. Her illness would
OL,16,Flater put a strain on our relationship
OL,17,Fbut the bond was never broken.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G13/17
