OL,3,CMum fears daughter's ME death could
OL,4,C'too easily' happen to someone else
OL,6,F"In her last birthday card she told me
OL,7,Fto relive the good times. She said 'I
OL,8,Falways wanted to get well enough to
OL,9,Fmake things better'.
OL,11,F"I always believed she would get
OL,12,Fbetter - I had daydreams about walking
OL,13,Falong the beach with her. She was
OL,14,Fbright, creative, articulated and
OL,15,Fopinionated.
OL,17,F"Imagine what a useful contribution
OL,18,Fshe could have made to our society
OL,19,Ftoday. I never for one moment thought
OL,20,FI would outlive her."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G14/17
