OL,3,CMum fears daughter's ME death could
OL,4,C'too easily' happen to someone else
OL,6,F"In contrast Maeve was weak, in pain
OL,7,Fand in danger of malnutrition. Only to
OL,8,Fbe told there was nothing that could
OL,9,Fbe done for her.
OL,11,F"Sarah was told to prepare for the
OL,12,Fworst - more than any other decision
OL,13,Fthis shocked me.
OL,15,F"A blunt refusal to treat an ill young
OL,16,Fwoman - in my view it was
OL,17,Fdiscriminatory. I believe with another
OL,18,Fcondition she would have been treated
OL,19,Fdifferently.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G16/17
